OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLabour plans to expand     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FLords despite abolition vow
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Labour has insisted it still wants to  
OL,6, abolish the Lords, despite planning to 
OL,7, increase its size by creating new peers
OL,8, if it wins the next election.          
OL,10,FSir Keir Starmer's spokesman said he   
OL,11,Fstood by a pledge to get rid of the    
OL,12,FLords during a first term in office,   
OL,13,Fbut there could be "interim reforms".  
OL,15,FCurrently, Labour would need 90 more   
OL,16,Fpeers to overtake the Conservatives'   
OL,17,F263 in the upper chamber.              
OL,19,FNew Labour peers would be expected to  
OL,20,Fback abolition, the spokesman said.    
